      "origin": "review_import",
      "note": "Documented the response shape convention in src/lib/server/apiResponses.ts: apiError always returns {error: string}; apiOk returns a domain-specific object with named keys (seriesData/events/abilities/deathEvents/fights/runs). The suggestion explicitly allows 'document explicit unwrapping rule'; wrapping everything in {data: ...} would force a breaking client refactor for no readability gain. New endpoints must extend this convention.",
