      "note": "Split src/lib/utils/recentCharacters.ts into a backend layer and a composition layer. New file src/lib/utils/recentCharactersBackends.ts defines RecentCharactersBackend interface (name + load() + add()) with a discriminated AddOutcome status ('ok' | 'unauthorized' | 'unavailable'). Two implementations: apiRecentCharactersBackend (POST/GET /api/recent-characters with proper status discrimination) and localStorageRecentCharactersBackend (with sameCharacter/MAX_RECENT/LOCAL_STORAGE_KEY constants). The composition layer (recentCharacters.ts) now only owns the two Svelte writable stores and the fallback policy: API first, fall back to localStorage when API is 'unavailable', do NOT mirror to localStorage on 'unauthorized' (so anonymous users don't accidentally persist). The store no longer reaches into fetch/localStorage directly. All existing consumers (apiForm.svelte, keystoneTable.svelte, recentCharacters.svelte) keep the same {subscribe, loading, init, add, clear} surface. npm run check passes.",
