      "origin": "review_import",
      "note": "Added a centralized handleApiError(scope, error, clientMessage?, status?) helper to src/lib/server/logger.ts. It logs the full error server-side via logServerError (which forwards the original error object so stack traces survive) and returns a sanitized {error: string} response via apiError. Migrated all 6 generic top-level catch blocks in routes/api to use it: death-hotspots, damage-average, spec-statistics, spec-top-players, top-players, browse-logs. Each now: 1) never silently discards the original error, 2) keeps the operator-side message in logs (with stack), 3) returns a 500 with a sanitized client-facing message (db handlers preserve the error.message-or-fallback used pre-refactor; spec/top-players use the existing 'Failed to fetch top players'). WCL handlers keep their two-branch pattern (WclQueryError vs unexpected) by design \u2014 graphql/http distinctions need the kind discriminator. JSDoc on handleApiError documents the convention. npm run check passes.",
