      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "note": "Fallbacks now signal degradation explicitly. (1) /api/character-score already returned source: 'blizzard' | 'raiderio' | null in its ScoreResult so callers can tell which provider answered (or that none did). (2) Refactored src/lib/utils/recentReports.ts to match the recentCharacters split: new recentReportsBackends.ts with apiRecentReportsBackend / localStorageRecentReportsBackend implementing a typed RecentReportsBackend interface and a discriminated AddRecentReportOutcome (status: 'ok' | 'unauthorized' | 'unavailable'). The composition layer never falls back on 'unauthorized' (anonymous user) \u2014 only on 'unavailable' (network/5xx). (3) Both recentCharacters and recentReports stores now expose a source: { subscribe } store of type 'api' | 'local-storage' | null so the UI can render a degraded-state indicator instead of silently swapping data sources. The clear() method also resets source to null. backwards-compatible {subscribe, loading, init, add/addReport, clear} surface preserved. npm run check passes.",
