      "note": "Reorganized src/lib/utils/ (which mixed 17+ files across 5+ unrelated domains) into 5 focused folders. New layout: src/lib/auth/ (oauth.ts, oauthBase.ts, blizzardOauth.ts, tokenCache.ts, blizzardTokenCache.ts), src/lib/data/ (characterData.ts, warcraftlogs.ts, myWowCharacters.ts, myWowRoster.ts, currentState.ts), src/lib/stores/ (recentCharacters.ts, recentCharactersBackends.ts, recentReports.ts, recentReportsBackends.ts), src/lib/calculations/ (keystoneCalculations.ts), src/lib/ui/ (chartCanvasPlugin.ts, wowheadTooltips.ts, classColors.ts, abilityMetadata.ts, abilityName.ts). Only clientLog.ts remains in utils/ as the genuine cross-cutting helper. Used git mv where files were tracked and plain mv for untracked, then sed-rewrote all 38 import sites under src/ from /utils/<file> to /<category>/<file>. Internal cross-imports stayed intra-cluster (oauth \u2192 oauthBase, tokenCache \u2192 oauth, blizzardTokenCache \u2192 blizzardOauth \u2192 oauthBase, recentCharacters \u2192 recentCharactersBackends) so no cross-folder coupling was introduced. Documented the new layout in DESIGN.md \u00a79 'Library Layout' with a folder-by-folder table and rules ('utils/ is a last resort'; 'server/ is server-only'; '/... aliases only'). Also re-added DESIGN.md \u00a78 'API Endpoint Naming' which had been lost in a stash mishap. Verification: npm run check passes 0/0; full vitest suite 49/49 pass.",
