      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "note": "The dual drizzle configs (drizzle.config.ts + drizzle.user.config.ts) are intentional \u2014 they manage migrations for two separate Postgres instances behind two different connection strings (DATABASE_URL for raid analytics, DATABASE_USER_URL for user/auth). Consolidation is not desired; the separation IS the deployment architecture. Documented the split: drizzle/README.md (NEW) explicitly maps each config to its schema (src/lib/db/schema.ts vs src/lib/db/userSchema.ts), its migration directory (drizzle/ vs drizzle/user/), its env var, and the role of each database. JSDoc headers on both schema files cross-reference both configs by name. DESIGN.md \u00a79 'Library Layout' lists both schemas under src/lib/db/. The orphan drizzle/schema.ts + drizzle/relations.ts that previously created ambiguity have been deleted. Each migration timeline therefore has exactly one Drizzle config, one schema TS file, and one migration directory \u2014 clearly documented end-to-end.",
