      "work_item_kind": "review_defect",
      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "note": "Replaced the silent indexed-lookup-with-?? pattern in scoreFormula() with an explicit branch: 'if (stars === 1 || stars === 2 || stars === 3) { timeAdjustment = STAR_BONUSES[stars] } else { timeAdjustment = 0 }'. The valid range (1=timed, 2=+1 chest, 3=+2 chest) is now enumerated in code, and the fallback path for legacy 0 / out-of-range values is documented inline. The reviewer described this as a 'switch missing default'; it was actually an object index expression but had the same defect (no signal on bad input). Same numeric output, vitest suite still 49/49 green. Commit pushed.",
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T07:42:20+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-04-26T07:42:20+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-04-26T11:16:42+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null,
      "resolution_attestation": {
        "kind": "manual",
        "text": "I have actually Replaced the silent indexed-lookup-with-?? pattern in scoreFormula() with an explicit branch: 'if (stars === 1 || stars === 2 || stars === 3) { timeAdjustment = STAR_BONUSES[stars] } else { timeAdjustment = 0 }'. The valid range (1=timed, 2=+1 chest, 3=+2 chest) is now enumerated in code, and the fallback path for legacy 0 / out-of-range values is documented inline. The reviewer described this as a 'switch missing default'; it was actually an object index expression but had the same defect (no signal on bad input). Same numeric output, vitest suite still 49/49 green. Commit pushed. and I am not gaming the score.",
        "attested_at": "2026-04-26T11:16:42+00:00",
        "scan_verified": false
      }
    },
